description.plain:
Alexander Gumuchian (b. June 30, 1995), better known by his stage name bbno$ (pronounced “baby no money”), is a rapper from Vancouver, British Columbia. Posting his first song “nah” in April of 2016, he ascended the ranks of SoundCloud rapidly, before moving to major streaming platforms.

bbno$ has dropped a variety of projects. The Baby Gravy EP (a collaborative EP with Yung Gravy), the whatever tape (a collaborative EP with duo So Loki), and his solo albums bb steps, recess, i don’t care at all, good luck have fun and eat ya veggies. bbno$ released a second collaborative album with Yung Gravy named Baby Gravy 2.

bbno$ is very well known in China and has done two sold-out tours in the country. This fame stems from a dance video posted by a popular Chinese dance group that used one of his earlier songs “Yoyo Tokyo.”



 One of bbno$’s shows in China

He also gained popularity throughout the rest of the world after his song “Lalala” with producer Y2K got used in a large number of videos and memes. The song peaked at 55 on the Hot 100 Billboard Chart, which is bbno$’s only Billboard charting place yet.

Frequent collaborators include Yung Gravy, Lentra, and So Loki.

songs.title: ​edamame

description.plain:
bbno$ and Rich Brian team up for the first time on “edamame”, a song produced by Diamond Pistols and the second single off of bbno$’s sixth album, eat ya veggies.

The song sees Alex and Brian rapping about finally getting paid for making hit songs and the popularity of their names and music. The song snippets were posted on both Alex’s and Brian’s Instagram stories a week before the release.

Besides the officially released version, there is an unreleased meme version of the song with bbno$ rapping over the Mii Channel melody.

songs.full_title: ​go gettas by ​bbno$ (Ft. ​andrei, Azteca, Killa Fonic & NANE)
songs.title: ​go gettas

description.plain:
Go Gettas is bbno$’s rap song featuring Killa Fonic, NANE and Azteca — some of the most popular Romanian rappers of all-time. As Azteca said on an Instagram live from May 15, 2020, this featuring was possible thanks to Jakoban (andrei), the producer of this song. Apparently, Jakoban was asked by bbno$ ‘what are the best Romanian rappers’.

Furthermore, this is the first time a Romanian rapper has collaborated with such a big artist from Canada (bbno$).

The official YouTube video was relased on May 15, 2020.

Go Gettas este colaborarea dintre bbno$, Killa Fonic, NANE și Azteca, care a fost posibilă datorită lui Jakoban (andrei), producer-ul acestei piese. Așa cum a explicat Azteca, pe un live pe Instagram în 15 mai 2020, care a avut loc cu puțin timp înainte de lansarea videoclipului oficial pe YouTube, bbno$ l-a întrebat pe Jakoban care sunt cei mai buni rapperi din România, astfel apărând această colaborare unică pentru rapperii români.

De asemenea, aceasta este prima colaborare cu un artist străin a lui Azteca și NANE lansată vreodată și prima colaborare a unor rapperi români cu un artist cunoscut din Canada.

Refrenul piesei este în limba engleză, cântat de bbno$, iar cele trei strofe sunt în limba română.

Videoclipul oficial a fost lansat pe YouTube în 15 mai 2020.
